	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 6th level, when you deal fire damage, you can wreathe yourself in protective flames until the end of your next turn. While wreathed:</p><ul><li><p>You gain resistance to fire damage.</p></li><li><p>The next time a creature hits you with a melee attack, it takes fire damage equal to your warlock level.</p></li></ul><p>Additionally, when you roll fire damage for a spell, you can reroll one damage die, but you must use the new roll.</p>",
